  <title>Cogl.MatrixStack.prototype.get_inverse</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function get_inverse(): [return_value: <link xref="Cogl.Bool">Cogl.Bool</link>, inverse: <link xref="Cogl.Matrix">Cogl.Matrix</link>] {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_matrix_stack_get_inverse()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Gets the inverse transform of the current matrix and uses it to
initialize a new <link xref="Cogl.Matrix"/>.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>return_value</code></title>
  <p><code>true</code> if the inverse was successfully calculated or <code>false</code>
  for degenerate transformations that can't be inverted (in this case the
  <code>inverse</code> matrix will simply be initialized with the identity matrix)</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>inverse</code></title>
  <p>The destination for a 4x4 inverse transformation matrix</p>
</item>
</terms>

